#Create a new project directory and open a terminal or command prompt inside that directory.

#Initialize a new Node.js project by running the following command:

npm init

#This will create a package.json file in your project directory.

#Install the required dependencies by running the following command:


npm install express sqlite3


#Run the server

node index.js

#access the server in a browser  http://localhost:3000/



#to access the db in dbeaver tool
1. download dbeaver  https://dbeaver.io/download/
2. run dbeaver.exe

3. in dbeaver click the new datbase cnnection
   select sqlite connection icon
   click next
   in the path inputbox enter the directory of the database.sqlite
    ex: C:\Edong\workspace\expressCRUDSQL\database.sqlite

    click finish


    